$interpreted: Rude Beast: Damn, I don't see 'em over here! Maybe they went that way! Let's go!
Soohyeon: ...I think we lost them...
Tindoiimu: Yeah...
Tindoiimu: ...Thank you for your help.
Beyata: Madam, I am honored I was able to repay you for helping me and the other girls before.
Beyata: Now, is this one injured?
Soohyeon: ......
Tindoiimu: She's fine. Thank you.
Tindoiimu: But you're bleeding... And that man just now in the alley...
Beyata: ......
Tindoiimu: He was the same customer that was bothering you before, wasn't he?
Beyata: Yes, he was.
Tindoiimu: Are you and him—
Beyata: Look here, you two. I've been nicknamed Bluebird, you know~
Soohyeon: Wow, what beautiful blue feathers...
Beyata: And I told him that I want to be his very own bluebird, and he accepted, and so I—
Beyata: I have to do all I can to make him the happiest man in the world, and make him feel so so so so good~
Tindoiimu: You...
Soohyeon: (Eh? Her whole personality just changed...)
Beyata: Because... those men have been so cold to us girls~
Beyata: I know me and the girls are just playthings, but... to be treated like that... it still hurts.
Tindoiimu: ...So you want revenge on that man?
Beyata: Revenge? No way, I'm his bluebird~
Beyata: Izumi said, men who don't treat their playthings with respect do it out of unhappiness. They don't have enough love in their lives~
Beyata: So it's up to me to give them so so so much love~
Tindoiimu: Izumi? He told you to do that?
Beyata: Well, not at first, but...
Beyata: I've always been on Hot Spring Street, you see... But at first, I was locked up, unable to move freely.
Soohyeon: What? That's so harsh...
Beyata: Then, one day, everything just became too much. I couldn't keep going any longer, so I fought back...
Tindoiimu: ......
Beyata: But... Izumi didn't punish me... In fact, he praised me.
Beyata: So... Whenever one of the men here gives us trouble, I show them love instead.
Soohyeon: But...
Tindoiimu: Don't you feel like you're being used?
Beyata: Used? How? When I bring my clients joy, I feel like I'm truly doing my job. Like I'm a true, beautiful bluebird...
Beyata: And then I feel that same love.
Beyata: Oh, look at me, just going on and on about myself! Please, forgive me~
Tindoiimu: That's fine, we...
Soohyeon: ......
Beyata: Now, where would you two ladies like to go?
Beyata: I'm familiar with all the little alleys around here. I can take you around safely and avoid those people from before.
Soohyeon: —The Red Palace!
Soohyeon: Can you bring me to the Red Palace? I... I've broken something, and I need them to help fix it!
Merchant: Eh? What are you two ladies still doing here?
Merchant: Everything's closing up, Red Palace included.
Tindoiimu: We're waiting for a friend.
Tindoiimu: She's asking on of the Red Palace artisans to help her fix her charm.
Merchant: Oh, you mean that girl wearing a veil?
Merchant: They already fixed her charm. I'm afraid she already left~
Beyata: But, I didn't see her come out? How did I miss her...
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: (She must have avoided us on purpose, left down another road. She must be nervous after I found out about her...)
Tindoiimu: Well, if she's already gone, then I'll be going too. I have some things to take care of. Thank you for bringing us over here.
Beyata: It's been my honor to help~
Tindoiimu: ...Thank you... Take care of yourself, now.
Beyata: ...You too... Stay happy...
